WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:35.618 position:50% align:center
[door opens]

00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:37.829 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Hello?

00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:40.665 position:50% align:center
Sorry. The rain's getting--

00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:42.792 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
I need an outfit tailored.

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:47.881 position:50% align:center
[TAILOR 12A] Unfortunately,
we only work on suits, sir.

00:00:47.964 --> 00:00:50.342 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] I have a once-in-a-
lifetime event coming up.

00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:52.677 position:50% align:center
I need proper attire.

00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:56.431 position:50% align:center
[TAILOR 12A] I see.
Is it a wedding, perchance?

00:00:57.432 --> 00:01:01.728 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] It's not.
But, you know. C'est la vie.

00:01:01.811 --> 00:01:04.147 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:02:40.744 --> 00:02:42.412 position:50% align:center
[REKI] Can you believe
it's happening?

00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:44.247 position:50% align:center
You're up against Adam.

00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:45.582 position:50% align:center
I know.

00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:47.417 position:50% align:center
Have you thought of
a strategy yet?

00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:48.835 position:50% align:center
You'll need one.

00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:52.881 position:50% align:center
Do you know why Adam
got into skating?

00:02:52.964 --> 00:02:54.174 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:02:55.216 --> 00:02:56.551 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:56.634 --> 00:02:58.303 position:50% align:center
I've never thought about it.

00:02:59.304 --> 00:03:02.098 position:50% align:center
I heard he's been alone
for a long time.

00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:04.934 position:50% align:center
It makes sense
with that personality.

00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:07.062 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
Anyway. I was just wondering.

00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:10.648 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
I guess he started because...

00:03:10.732 --> 00:03:12.442 position:50% align:center
Well, because it's fun.

00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:13.985 position:50% align:center
I mean there's not really
any other reason

00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.862 position:50% align:center
to get into it, right?

00:03:17.447 --> 00:03:18.907 position:50% align:center
That's true.

00:03:20.617 --> 00:03:23.495 position:50% align:center
This is what's called
a search warrant!

00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:26.998 position:50% align:center
Which means I have full access
to Shindo's estate!

00:03:28.166 --> 00:03:30.210 position:50% align:center
[MIYA] Your injuries
healed suspiciously fast.

00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:32.712 position:50% align:center
I can't sleep my life
away in a hospital.

00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:34.089 position:50% align:center
Amen to that.

00:03:34.172 --> 00:03:36.716 position:50% align:center
So? Do we think Langa
can win this thing?

00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:37.842 position:50% align:center
I thought he did pretty well

00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:40.178 position:50% align:center
in that match he was
in the other day.

00:03:40.261 --> 00:03:42.806 position:50% align:center
But Adam wasn't
fully invested then.

00:03:42.889 --> 00:03:44.307 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:03:44.391 --> 00:03:47.727 position:50% align:center
You guys have probably seen
him skate at his max a lot.

00:03:47.811 --> 00:03:50.271 position:50% align:center
[CHERRY]
Nope. Not one time.

00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:52.107 position:50% align:center
He's never felt the need
to go out of his way

00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:54.526 position:50% align:center
to prove himself to anyone.

00:03:58.863 --> 00:04:01.324 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
All right. That should do it.

00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:04.077 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
You finished it.

00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:07.997 position:50% align:center
Wow. You're so talented.

00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.958 position:50% align:center
It's beautiful.

00:04:10.041 --> 00:04:12.085 position:50% align:center
[REKI] Oh man. Do you
remember the first time

00:04:12.168 --> 00:04:13.378 position:50% align:center
you got on a board?

00:04:13.461 --> 00:04:15.505 position:50% align:center
Of course!
I couldn't do anything

00:04:15.588 --> 00:04:17.966 position:50% align:center
unless both my feet were
duct taped to the deck.

00:04:18.049 --> 00:04:21.803 position:50% align:center
The epitome of ridiculous,
but still always an epic skater.

00:04:21.886 --> 00:04:23.763 position:50% align:center
I couldn't even do
a single push.

00:04:23.847 --> 00:04:25.265 position:50% align:center
Holy crap, that's right!

00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:27.392 position:50% align:center
You were scooting
with your hands!

00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:31.021 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
Reki. I'm grateful for you.

00:04:34.149 --> 00:04:36.443 position:50% align:center
Switching out the boards like
this was an incredible favor.

00:04:36.526 --> 00:04:37.444 position:50% align:center
You're grateful for that?

00:04:37.527 --> 00:04:39.320 position:50% align:center
[LANGA laughs]

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:41.656 position:50% align:center
Go get 'im.

00:04:43.241 --> 00:04:47.620 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
Hey. When the finals are over...

00:04:56.463 --> 00:04:57.505 position:50% align:center
What the hell?

00:04:57.589 --> 00:04:59.841 position:50% align:center
Something's up,
this isn't normal.

00:04:59.924 --> 00:05:02.385 position:50% align:center
You'll have to
walk it from here, folks!

00:05:03.386 --> 00:05:04.471 position:50% align:center
I'll be okay.

00:05:04.554 --> 00:05:07.015 position:50% align:center
I'm sure they're
making Adam walk, too.

00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:08.433 position:50% align:center
[SKATERS chattering]

00:05:08.516 --> 00:05:10.185 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12A] Is that the
finish line for this one?

00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:12.062 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12B]
Looks like a gravestone.

00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:17.025 position:50% align:center
[bell tolls]

00:05:17.108 --> 00:05:19.778 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
What is up with that course?

00:05:19.861 --> 00:05:21.654 position:50% align:center
If they slip off the track,
they're dead for sure.

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:24.366 position:50% align:center
Why'd we trade the normal
course for a deathtrap?

00:05:24.449 --> 00:05:26.076 position:50% align:center
[TADASHI] The entrance
to the abandoned factory

00:05:26.159 --> 00:05:28.119 position:50% align:center
got sealed off due to the storm.

00:05:28.203 --> 00:05:30.538 position:50% align:center
Adam asked for this
as a replacement.

00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:34.167 position:50% align:center
We used this back in the day.
When "S" first started.

00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:37.295 position:50% align:center
It was deemed too dangerous
and got banned.

00:05:37.379 --> 00:05:39.964 position:50% align:center
He said it was
appropriate for tonight.

00:05:41.007 --> 00:05:42.425 position:50% align:center
Langa...

00:05:58.566 --> 00:06:00.735 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12C] I've never seen
Adam show up like that before.

00:06:00.819 --> 00:06:02.487 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12A] Is that board
shaped like a coffin?

00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:05.824 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12D] Does that mean
someone's gonna die?

00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:12.038 position:50% align:center
Welcome, Snow.

00:06:12.122 --> 00:06:14.374 position:50% align:center
I've been waiting for you.

00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:16.710 position:50% align:center
Adam.

00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:20.755 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Do you like the look?

00:06:20.839 --> 00:06:24.968 position:50% align:center
I felt it was the most suitable
of outfits for tonight.

00:06:25.051 --> 00:06:27.679 position:50% align:center
For our little danse macabre.

00:06:32.434 --> 00:06:37.313 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] Tonight. We tango
where no one can interfere.

00:06:37.397 --> 00:06:40.775 position:50% align:center
A world that was
created just for us.

00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:50.702 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12E]
Adam's ahead!

00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:53.538 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12F] He's bookin'
it hard! More than usual!

00:07:03.131 --> 00:07:06.301 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] There's no denying
he's a phenomenal skater.

00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:09.012 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Follow me!

00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:11.431 position:50% align:center
Something tells me
you can keep up.

00:07:16.936 --> 00:07:18.271 position:50% align:center
I got this!

00:07:21.858 --> 00:07:22.984 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
Stay on track, bro!

00:07:23.068 --> 00:07:24.235 position:50% align:center
He's gonna fall!

00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:26.404 position:50% align:center
Langa! Do it!

00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:31.534 position:50% align:center
[LANGA gasps]
Wait, what happened to Adam?

00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:33.203 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Peek a boo, angel.

00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:34.996 position:50% align:center
I jumped right after you.

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:37.374 position:50% align:center
Kindred minds think alike.

00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:39.918 position:50% align:center
[REKI] Langa always
pulls ahead in the air!

00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:44.673 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] You're gonna have to try
a lot harder than that! Tragic.

00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:57.477 position:50% align:center
It's a combination attack!

00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:59.104 position:50% align:center
Dodge it, dude!

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:08.863 position:50% align:center
[ADAM chuckles]

00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:13.535 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Very good! Keep pushing!

00:08:13.618 --> 00:08:16.830 position:50% align:center
You can have anything you want
if you push your own limits.

00:08:16.913 --> 00:08:18.373 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12G]
They're both out of control.

00:08:18.456 --> 00:08:20.625 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12H]
The camera can't keep up.

00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:22.836 position:50% align:center
Just how fast do they wanna go?

00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:24.337 position:50% align:center
It's too dangerous.

00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:27.257 position:50% align:center
If they stray off the main line
at all, they'll crash.

00:08:28.883 --> 00:08:30.093 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
C'mon.

00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:45.859 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
I gotta go faster! Faster!

00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:47.527 position:50% align:center
That's it.

00:08:47.610 --> 00:08:50.447 position:50% align:center
Right here. Right now!

00:08:57.245 --> 00:09:01.416 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] In that moment, the
course around us disappeared.

00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:02.959 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
We made it, Langa.

00:09:03.043 --> 00:09:06.129 position:50% align:center
A world that belongs only to us!

00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:08.465 position:50% align:center
Look around, no one else here.

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:12.427 position:50% align:center
Isn't it wonderful?
Destiny sent you to me.

00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:15.180 position:50% align:center
Forget your boring life.

00:09:15.263 --> 00:09:17.724 position:50% align:center
We're meant to live like kings!

00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:19.684 position:50% align:center
"Boring life"?

00:09:19.768 --> 00:09:22.103 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
No more cruel expectations.

00:09:22.187 --> 00:09:24.522 position:50% align:center
No one giving you orders.

00:09:25.482 --> 00:09:27.067 position:50% align:center
In this life,
the only commitment

00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:29.861 position:50% align:center
you'll have is to
the thrill of skating.

00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:33.698 position:50% align:center
You can forget anything
and everything else.

00:09:33.782 --> 00:09:35.700 position:50% align:center
Why would I forget?

00:09:38.828 --> 00:09:41.122 position:50% align:center
[CARLA] A new interval
record has been set.

00:09:41.206 --> 00:09:42.248 position:50% align:center
You gotta be kidding!

00:09:42.332 --> 00:09:43.416 position:50% align:center
That's crazy!

00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:45.335 position:50% align:center
They're on totally
different levels!

00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:46.795 position:50% align:center
Impossible.

00:09:46.878 --> 00:09:48.880 position:50% align:center
Unless they're both
in the zone right now.

00:09:48.963 --> 00:09:50.465 position:50% align:center
The zone?

00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:53.677 position:50% align:center
It's a state of being that can
happen for the best athletes.

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.178 position:50% align:center
Like when batters
can't see anything

00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:57.013 position:50% align:center
but the ball
heading toward them.

00:09:57.097 --> 00:09:58.640 position:50% align:center
They're concentrating
so intensely

00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:00.558 position:50% align:center
everything else goes dark.

00:10:00.642 --> 00:10:02.060 position:50% align:center
Oh wow.

00:10:03.186 --> 00:10:05.146 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
You don't want anything.

00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:07.440 position:50% align:center
You don't need anything.

00:10:07.524 --> 00:10:08.858 position:50% align:center
"Anything"?

00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:12.529 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
That's right. Forget all of it.

00:10:12.612 --> 00:10:16.741 position:50% align:center
Every last thing
in your past. Let it go.

00:10:16.825 --> 00:10:20.453 position:50% align:center
Forget everything. Let go.

00:10:25.709 --> 00:10:27.002 position:50% align:center
A crack!

00:10:29.754 --> 00:10:32.132 position:50% align:center
The hell? Did he not see that?

00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:33.883 position:50% align:center
He's gotta be in the zone.

00:10:33.967 --> 00:10:36.386 position:50% align:center
It might be suicide if
he doesn't snap out of it.

00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:37.554 position:50% align:center
Like how?

00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.681 position:50% align:center
How's he supposed to
get back to normal?

00:10:39.764 --> 00:10:40.974 position:50% align:center
I don't know.

00:10:41.057 --> 00:10:42.976 position:50% align:center
I've never been in that state.

00:10:43.059 --> 00:10:44.811 position:50% align:center
You gotta come back, Langa!

00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:48.106 position:50% align:center
I don't know what's going on,
but this is not how you skate!

00:10:55.905 --> 00:11:00.535 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] It's all white.
I can't see anything.

00:11:00.618 --> 00:11:02.620 position:50% align:center
I can't hear anything.

00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:06.041 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
I don't feel anything.

00:11:07.125 --> 00:11:09.461 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
It's just like that other time.

00:11:11.254 --> 00:11:13.506 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
The days after Dad died.

00:11:14.924 --> 00:11:17.594 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] I didn't feel
a single emotion.

00:11:19.054 --> 00:11:21.848 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
And nothing was fun anymore.

00:11:35.653 --> 00:11:37.113 position:50% align:center
It's breaking!

00:11:38.323 --> 00:11:40.909 position:50% align:center
Langa!

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:50.919 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
Am I flying? Or falling.

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:54.589 position:50% align:center
Does this mean I'm gonna die?

00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:10.730 position:50% align:center
[LANGA gasps]

00:12:14.526 --> 00:12:16.027 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
That's right.

00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:21.324 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
Skating is...

00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:28.540 position:50% align:center
...fun!

00:12:40.135 --> 00:12:41.177 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12I]
No frikkin way!

00:12:41.261 --> 00:12:42.637 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12J]
He's skating down a cliff!

00:12:42.721 --> 00:12:43.888 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12K]
Snow, you're the man!

00:12:43.972 --> 00:12:45.390 position:50% align:center
That dude's somethin' else!

00:12:45.473 --> 00:12:47.350 position:50% align:center
Simply unpredictable.

00:12:47.434 --> 00:12:51.396 position:50% align:center
Yes. Langa's frikkin'
back, my dudes!

00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:55.775 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:01.698 --> 00:13:04.576 position:50% align:center
You enjoying yourself? Kiddo?

00:13:07.996 --> 00:13:10.165 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I really am, Dad.

00:13:22.886 --> 00:13:24.346 position:50% align:center
Little Langa?

00:13:24.429 --> 00:13:25.472 position:50% align:center
Where are you?

00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:26.973 position:50% align:center
Where'd you go?

00:13:27.057 --> 00:13:32.270 position:50% align:center
Are you gonna run away
from me, too? Langa!

00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:38.985 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
It was all a lie.

00:13:39.069 --> 00:13:42.530 position:50% align:center
Eve never existed
in the first place.

00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:44.574 position:50% align:center
Just emptiness.

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:48.453 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
I have no one on my side.

00:13:48.536 --> 00:13:49.954 position:50% align:center
No one.

00:13:53.875 --> 00:13:55.794 position:50% align:center
This isn't what it's about.

00:14:00.548 --> 00:14:04.386 position:50% align:center
Stop! How dare you drag me back
into an insignificant world!

00:14:04.469 --> 00:14:05.929 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
I want to help you!

00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:08.139 position:50% align:center
I'll show you
how fun skating can be!

00:14:08.223 --> 00:14:09.766 position:50% align:center
Help me?

00:14:09.849 --> 00:14:11.726 position:50% align:center
I've learned that
skating builds bonds.

00:14:11.810 --> 00:14:12.936 position:50% align:center
That don't break.

00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:14.145 position:50% align:center
It's not worth having a board

00:14:14.229 --> 00:14:15.772 position:50% align:center
unless you have
friends at your side.

00:14:15.855 --> 00:14:20.026 position:50% align:center
Please. Friends only exist
to teach you about betrayal.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:21.486 position:50% align:center
You want to believe
in your idea of

00:14:21.569 --> 00:14:23.446 position:50% align:center
what a relationship should be.

00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:26.157 position:50% align:center
Because you are
an ignorant child!

00:14:26.241 --> 00:14:28.243 position:50% align:center
Then I guess you
must be a child, too.

00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:29.828 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Please explain.

00:14:29.911 --> 00:14:31.621 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
You want a friend to skate with.

00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:35.125 position:50% align:center
I have long since rid myself
of insignificant dreams!

00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:38.169 position:50% align:center
Then why do you keep insisting
on taking me with you?

00:14:39.546 --> 00:14:41.172 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
You desire something real.

00:14:41.256 --> 00:14:43.341 position:50% align:center
Shut up.

00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:45.760 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
You're tired of being alone.

00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:48.179 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
I told you to shut up!

00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:53.810 position:50% align:center
Can't have a good argument
all by yourself, now can you?

00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:55.770 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Quit trying to confuse me!

00:14:55.854 --> 00:14:58.565 position:50% align:center
Nobody knows what
I want or how I feel!

00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:01.901 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
And no one ever will!

00:15:01.985 --> 00:15:03.695 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Langa!

00:15:03.778 --> 00:15:04.612 position:50% align:center
C'mon!

00:15:04.696 --> 00:15:07.449 position:50% align:center
[ADAM yells]

00:15:07.532 --> 00:15:10.243 position:50% align:center
[LANGA yells]

00:15:20.462 --> 00:15:22.088 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12L] Doesn't look
like they're moving.

00:15:22.172 --> 00:15:24.049 position:50% align:center
[TAILOR 12A]
Do you think they're okay?

00:15:24.132 --> 00:15:25.633 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
Hold it!

00:15:25.717 --> 00:15:26.843 position:50% align:center
I have to help!

00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.053 position:50% align:center
[REKI]
He'll get up.

00:15:28.136 --> 00:15:29.429 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:15:29.512 --> 00:15:30.930 position:50% align:center
I'm sure.

00:15:33.558 --> 00:15:35.143 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:15:35.226 --> 00:15:37.645 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12N]
Snow's starting to move!

00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:46.905 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12O]
So is Adam!

00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:48.198 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12P]
Who'll be faster?

00:15:48.281 --> 00:15:50.033 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:15:50.116 --> 00:15:51.785 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Stand up!

00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:55.288 position:50% align:center
Stand up and teach
that idiot a lesson!

00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:56.915 position:50% align:center
Langa!

00:15:58.708 --> 00:16:00.460 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
This is not defeat!

00:16:00.543 --> 00:16:03.171 position:50% align:center
That is unacceptable
in this house!

00:16:04.047 --> 00:16:06.341 position:50% align:center
Mr. Ainosuke.

00:16:06.424 --> 00:16:07.676 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12Q]
Snow, you magnificent beast!

00:16:07.759 --> 00:16:09.761 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12R]
Kill him, Snow!

00:16:14.432 --> 00:16:15.725 position:50% align:center
You ready?

00:16:21.439 --> 00:16:22.440 position:50% align:center
[TADASHI]
Do you wanna try?

00:16:22.524 --> 00:16:24.442 position:50% align:center
I can show you how.

00:16:24.526 --> 00:16:27.028 position:50% align:center
It's no fun to do
all by yourself.

00:16:43.962 --> 00:16:45.296 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12S]
The beef is on!

00:16:45.380 --> 00:16:46.881 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12T] We're gonna
see the final showdown!

00:16:46.965 --> 00:16:49.259 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12U]
I love you, Snow!

00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:21.624 position:50% align:center
Those are some clutch
moves. I'm impressed.

00:17:21.708 --> 00:17:25.795 position:50% align:center
They're way too reckless. But...

00:17:25.879 --> 00:17:29.007 position:50% align:center
I know, but it looks
like so much fun!

00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:36.222 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
Damnit! This is a waste of time!

00:17:36.306 --> 00:17:37.807 position:50% align:center
You want to enjoy yourself?

00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:39.642 position:50% align:center
That won't change your life!

00:17:39.726 --> 00:17:42.812 position:50% align:center
If you don't win,
you will cease to exist!

00:17:42.896 --> 00:17:45.231 position:50% align:center
You won't be loved!

00:17:45.315 --> 00:17:48.109 position:50% align:center
I will win. Watch me.

00:17:54.741 --> 00:17:55.784 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12V]
Adam pulled in front again!

00:17:55.867 --> 00:17:57.744 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12W]
Snow, are you awake?

00:17:57.827 --> 00:18:00.121 position:50% align:center
Mr. Ainosuke!

00:18:00.205 --> 00:18:01.456 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:18:01.539 --> 00:18:03.333 position:50% align:center
When are you going to
take this seriously, Adam?

00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:05.502 position:50% align:center
Give it up already. I'm bored!

00:18:05.585 --> 00:18:07.087 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12X]
So close to the finish line!

00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:08.505 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12Y]
They're basically there!

00:18:08.588 --> 00:18:09.381 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12B]
Who's winning?

00:18:09.464 --> 00:18:11.591 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12Z]
Hurry! Pass him!

00:18:15.762 --> 00:18:17.806 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12AA]
Here they come! It's Snow!

00:18:17.889 --> 00:18:21.518 position:50% align:center
No wait, it's Adam!
I can't tell!

00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:25.146 position:50% align:center
Langa!

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:28.900 position:50% align:center
[BOTH yelling]

00:18:41.913 --> 00:18:43.206 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12AB]
Snow wins the race!

00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:44.290 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12AC]
Adam has been defeated!

00:18:44.374 --> 00:18:47.043 position:50% align:center
[SKATER 12AD]
The legend has fallen!

00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:50.588 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
Reki?

00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:54.718 position:50% align:center
Who won? You can be honest.

00:18:57.095 --> 00:19:00.223 position:50% align:center
Why are you an idiot?
It was you!

00:19:00.306 --> 00:19:01.891 position:50% align:center
You won, bro!

00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:03.893 position:50% align:center
Yep! And it was awesome!

00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:07.188 position:50% align:center
[SHADOW]
My man.

00:19:07.272 --> 00:19:10.066 position:50% align:center
Talk about an epic finale.

00:19:10.150 --> 00:19:12.652 position:50% align:center
You've got a gift, so don't
ever sell yourself short.

00:19:12.736 --> 00:19:14.738 position:50% align:center
You're the first to beat Adam.

00:19:14.821 --> 00:19:17.532 position:50% align:center
I think you might be my hero
after pulling that off.

00:19:17.615 --> 00:19:20.744 position:50% align:center
Tonight I'm gonna
drink until I puke!

00:19:22.328 --> 00:19:25.081 position:50% align:center
[ALL laughing]

00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.421 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry, sir.

00:19:39.054 --> 00:19:41.723 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] I thought I gave
all that up long ago.

00:19:46.978 --> 00:19:48.980 position:50% align:center
[ADAM]
But he reminded me.

00:19:49.064 --> 00:19:51.274 position:50% align:center
Everything I learned from you.

00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:53.777 position:50% align:center
Back when we were little kids.

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.028 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:37.380 position:50% align:center
A transfer?

00:21:37.464 --> 00:21:40.675 position:50% align:center
[MATSUMURA] A promotion.
You can go back to Tokyo now.

00:21:40.759 --> 00:21:44.179 position:50% align:center
But Mr. Matsumura, wait, I'm not
done investigating Shindo!

00:21:44.262 --> 00:21:45.889 position:50% align:center
And you don't need to be.

00:21:45.972 --> 00:21:48.600 position:50% align:center
That's outside
your jurisdiction now.

00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:51.936 position:50% align:center
Understood, sir.

00:21:53.355 --> 00:21:54.981 position:50% align:center
Just a token of appreciation for

00:21:55.065 --> 00:21:57.734 position:50% align:center
the leaks you dropped
on Member Takano.

00:21:57.817 --> 00:21:59.819 position:50% align:center
That's quite helpful.
Thank you, sir.

00:21:59.903 --> 00:22:03.698 position:50% align:center
I think things are gonna
work out just fine.

00:22:03.782 --> 00:22:05.533 position:50% align:center
[MATSUMURA]
If you'll excuse me.

00:22:07.118 --> 00:22:09.871 position:50% align:center
So did you really
sell out Mr. Takano?

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:11.873 position:50% align:center
Listen, I did what I
had to do, all right?

00:22:11.956 --> 00:22:15.126 position:50% align:center
With the old man gone now,
I'm officially the top dog here.

00:22:15.210 --> 00:22:17.087 position:50% align:center
Yes, I understand,
but something like that

00:22:17.170 --> 00:22:19.506 position:50% align:center
could cause you to be
charged with perjury.

00:22:19.589 --> 00:22:20.924 position:50% align:center
Well, it would look
quite suspicious

00:22:21.007 --> 00:22:23.093 position:50% align:center
if I didn't take on
a little heat myself.

00:22:23.176 --> 00:22:26.971 position:50% align:center
But you had told me you
expected me to take the blame.

00:22:27.055 --> 00:22:30.225 position:50% align:center
[ADAM] Did you think I'd
release you from your collar?

00:22:30.308 --> 00:22:34.187 position:50% align:center
Silly pup. You're still mine
for the rest of our lives.

00:22:38.191 --> 00:22:39.442 position:50% align:center
'Kay.

00:22:44.114 --> 00:22:45.740 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] Reki told me
about this superhero

00:22:45.824 --> 00:22:47.784 position:50% align:center
he used to watch on TV.

00:22:47.867 --> 00:22:49.953 position:50% align:center
He said he scared him a little.

00:22:51.204 --> 00:22:52.872 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] The reason was
because after each episode

00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:55.458 position:50% align:center
he asked,
"What makes you happy?"

00:22:58.294 --> 00:23:00.422 position:50% align:center
[LANGA] At first,
I thought Reki was nuts.

00:23:00.505 --> 00:23:02.882 position:50% align:center
What's so scary about that?

00:23:02.966 --> 00:23:06.052 position:50% align:center
But now, I think I kinda get it.

00:23:06.136 --> 00:23:08.972 position:50% align:center
It's scary not to
know the answer.

00:23:09.055 --> 00:23:11.725 position:50% align:center
To have nothing
that makes you happy.

00:23:11.808 --> 00:23:15.645 position:50% align:center
I've been there.
But not anymore.

00:23:15.729 --> 00:23:17.981 position:50% align:center
I know what makes me happy.

00:23:21.985 --> 00:23:24.446 position:50% align:center
[LANGA]
I understand true joy.

00:23:32.704 --> 00:23:35.123 position:50% align:center
We can finally make good
on that promise.

00:23:35.206 --> 00:23:39.044 position:50% align:center
Yeah. We're gonna skate
the final race together.

00:23:39.127 --> 00:23:41.671 position:50% align:center
Don't go easy on me.

00:23:41.755 --> 00:23:43.506 position:50% align:center
Right back atcha.

00:23:47.010 --> 00:23:48.470 position:50% align:center
[REKI, LANGA]
Ready...